---
// Owner Introduction Component
// Introduces Kim & Bryan to build trust with visitors
---

<section class="py-16 md:py-20 bg-white" id="meet-owners">
  <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">

      <!-- Section Header -->
      <div class="text-center mb-10">
        <span class="font-hand text-brand-orange text-xl -rotate-2 inline-block mb-2">
          Family-Owned Since 2008
        </span>
        <h2 class="font-display font-black text-3xl md:text-4xl text-brand-brown">
          Meet Kim & Bryan
        </h2>
      </div>

      <div class="flex flex-col md:flex-row items-center gap-8 md:gap-12">

        <!-- Photo placeholder - will use real photo when available -->
        <div class="w-48 h-48 md:w-64 md:h-64 rounded-full bg-stone-200 border-4 border-brand-orange/30 overflow-hidden flex-shrink-0 shadow-lg">
          <!-- Placeholder with initials until real photo -->
          <div class="w-full h-full flex items-center justify-center bg-brand-brown/10">
            <span class="font-display font-bold text-4xl md:text-5xl text-brand-brown/40">K&B</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Bio Text -->
        <div class="text-center md:text-left">
          <p class="text-lg text-stone-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            We're Kim and Bryan Utt, and we've been serving hunters, anglers, and outdoor
            folks in Braxton County for over 15 years. What started as a small sporting
            goods shop in the New River Gorge area has grown into your local source for
            firearms, ammo, fishing tackle, and everything you need for the woods.
          </p>

          <p class="text-lg text-stone-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            We live in Sutton, worship at Tesla Church, and know these hills like the
            back of our hands. When you stop by, you're not just another customer â€”
            you're a neighbor.
          </p>

          <p class="text-stone-500 italic">
            "We own the building. We own every single thing in it. That's God."
          </p>

          <div class="mt-6">
            <a
              href="/story"
              class="inline-flex items-center text-sign-green font-bold hover:text-brand-brown transition-colors"
            >
              Read Our Full Story
              <svg class="w-4 h-4 ml-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7"></path>
              </svg>
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
